label.value: Prostatic Fluid

value.value: A slightly alkaline fluid produced by the prostate gland. It contributes 20-30% of the total volume of seminal fluid.

label.value: Thousand Copies per Milliliter

value.value: The unit of concentration expressed as the number of 10 to the third power copies in unit volume equal to one milliliter.

label.value: Million Copies per Milliliter

value.value: The unit of concentration expressed as the number of 10 to the sixth power copies in unit volume equal to one milliliter.

label.value: Diopter

value.value: A unit of measurement of the optical power of a curved mirror or lens represented by the inverse of the focal length in meters.

label.value: Ethyleneimine

value.value: A monofunctional alkylating agent with potential antineoplastic activity.  Reacting with DNA mainly at guanine and adenine residues, ethylenimine alkylates DNA, thereby producing DNA interstrand crosslinks and DNA breaks, and interfering with DNA replication and cell division. (NCI04)
